{"id":"couch","term":"Couch","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 49:4\">Gen. 49:4</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 5:1\">1 Chr. 5:1</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Job 7:13\">Job 7:13</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 6:6\">Ps. 6:6</a>, etc.), a seat for repose or rest. (See BED.)</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 49:4","1 Chronicles 5:1","Job 7:13","Psalms 6:6"]}